		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Nelson A. Smith</strong></span> is a freelance advertising writer and essayist living in Manhattan. His work has appeared in <em>Harper&rsquo;s</em>, the <em>New York Times Magazine</em>, the <em>Baffler</em>, <em>In These Times</em>, and elsewhere. He is currently working on a cultural history of pigeons, from Genesis to Darwin to Skinner, tentatively titled &ldquo;Lessons of an Organic Widget.&rdquo;</p><a href="/contributors/nelson-a-smith" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
